# 040 — graph-runtime

## Purpose

`graph-runtime` executes validated `GraphDefinition` objects. It is framework-agnostic.

## Core abstractions

- `NodeHandler<TInput, TOutput>` — pure async function executed for a node
- `NodeRegistry` — maps node type names to `NodeHandler` implementations
- `ConditionRegistry` — maps condition names to pure boolean functions over `GraphState`
- `Checkpointer` — persists and restores `GraphState` snapshots
- `InMemoryCheckpointer` — default in-memory implementation for tests
- `EventBus` — emits lifecycle events (node_started, node_completed, node_failed, run_suspended, run_resumed, run_completed)
- `InMemoryEventBus` — default in-memory implementation
- `GraphRuntime` — orchestrates sequential execution, checkpointing, eventing

## Rules

- Checkpoint after every node completion and every state mutation.
- Emit events for every node lifecycle transition.
- Human gate nodes must suspend the run cleanly and emit `run_suspended`.
- Resume must restore from the latest checkpoint.
- Retry policy is defined per node in `NodeDefinition`; runtime enforces it.
- No NestJS decorators, no React, no HTTP in this package.
- All features must have Vitest unit tests.
- Parallel execution and subgraphs are future phases — reserve the interface, do not implement yet.